I&#x27;m looking for language that can be described like &quot;C with classes&quot;. Simplicity of C and some basic OOP features in one. Not Go and not C++. Simple low-level language without garbage collector and with C libs support.<p>I&#x27;ve tried to imagine it as some kind of preprocessor with C files as output.<p>Fow example this:<p><pre><code>    struct Test {
        int testFunc(int a) { return a * a; }
       ...
    };

    int main() {
        Test t;
        return t.testFunc(2);
    }
</code></pre>
Can be transformed to C code:<p><pre><code>    struct Test {
        ...
    };

    int Test_testFunc_int_int(Test * this, int a) {
        return a * a;
    }

    int main() {
        Test t;
        return Test_testFunc_int_int(&t, 2);
    }
</code></pre>
Does anyone know language or meta-language (with output as C files) or some libs maybe similar to this?
